com.github.jonathanxd.iutils.type

Class TypeInfo<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.jonathanxd.iutils.type.TypeInfo<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<TypeInfo>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractTypeInfo, ConcreteTypeInfo, DynamicTypeInfo

    public class TypeInfo<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<TypeInfo>
    Holds information about generic types. TypeInfo does not hold information about wildcard types, and this behavior is intentional. TypeInfo is invariant.

      • getTypeParameter

        public TypeInfo<?> getTypeParameter(int pos)
                             throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                                    java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException
        Gets information of type parameter in position pos. Example, for Map<String, Integer>, getTypeParameter(1) returns Integer type info.
        Parameters:
        pos - Position.
        Returns:
        Information of type parameter in position pos.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If pos is negative.
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - If pos exceeds the amount of type parameters in type class.

      • getTypeParameter

        public TypeInfo<?> getTypeParameter(java.lang.String name)
                             throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Gets the type parameter information by name of type variable of type class. Example, for Map<String, Integer>, which is declared as Map<K, V>, getTypeParameter("V") return Integer type info.
        Parameters:
        name - Name of type variable of type class.
        Returns:
        Type parameter information corresponding to type variable with specified name.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If there is no type variable with specified name in type class.

      • compareTypeAndRelatedTo

        public int compareTypeAndRelatedTo(TypeInfo compareTo)
        Restrictively compare current type and related types to type and related types of another TypeInfo. This method only works for types that are cached or available from the TypeInfo class loader context. If types are not available from the class loader, call the loadTypes(Function) method to load them.
        Parameters:
        compareTo - Element to compare
        Returns:
        0 if comparison succeed, positive or negative number if not.
